From 525e71775d7f124f35dcfd8d8abf8c10e72b112a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kgoncalv <kayo.goncalvesdacosta@windriver.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 09:33:23 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add Ceilometer metrics Services and ServiceMonitors

Expose Ceilometer central and compute agent metrics to a
Prometheus Operator deployment by adding headless metrics
Services, matching ServiceMonitor CRDs, and the foundational
values they depend on.

New templates:
  - templates/service-central-metrics.yaml
  - templates/service-compute-metrics.yaml
  - templates/servicemonitor-central.yaml
  - templates/servicemonitor-compute.yaml

Metrics Services:
  - Headless (clusterIP: None) Services named
    <release>-central and <release>-compute
  - Named "metrics" port 9101 (targetPort 9101, TCP)
  - Select pods via application=ceilometer with component
    central/compute
  - Gated on manifest toggles

ServiceMonitors:
  - monitoring.coreos.com/v1 ServiceMonitor CRDs selecting
    Services labeled app=ceilometer-central/compute
  - Scrape "metrics" port at /metrics, scoped to the release
    namespace
  - Set app and job labels to ceilometer-central/-compute
  - Source interval/timeout from
    .Values.servicemonitor.central|compute.scrape_interval
    and scrape_timeout (default 30s/10s)
  - Gated on .Capabilities.APIVersions and manifests toggles

values.yaml additions:

  servicemonitor:
    central:
      scrape_interval: 30s
      scrape_timeout: 10s
    compute:
      scrape_interval: 30s
      scrape_timeout: 10s
  manifests:
    service_central_metrics: true
    service_compute_metrics: true
    servicemonitor_central: true
    servicemonitor_compute: true
Co-authored-by: cbohlhal <Caique.BohlhalterdeSouza@windriver.com>
Signed-off-by: kgoncalv <kayo.goncalvesdacosta@windriver.com>
---
 .../templates/service-central-metrics.yaml    | 33 +++++++++++++++++
 .../templates/service-compute-metrics.yaml    | 33 +++++++++++++++++
 .../templates/servicemonitor-central.yaml     | 37 +++++++++++++++++++
 .../templates/servicemonitor-compute.yaml     | 37 +++++++++++++++++++
 ceilometer/values.yaml                        | 12 ++++++
